## 5. Results

**Final Model Performance (Test Set)**

| Metric    | Value  | What it means                         |
| --------- | ------ | ------------------------------------- |
| Accuracy  | 0.9686 | Percentage of correct predictions     |
| Precision | 1.0000 | All predicted spam were actually spam |
| Recall    | 0.7667 | Model detected ~76.7% of actual spam  |
| F1 Score  | 0.8679 | Balance between precision and recall  |

---

### Confusion Matrix

|             | Predicted Ham | Predicted Spam |
| ----------- | ------------- | -------------- |
| Actual Ham  | 961 (TN)      | 4 (FP)         |
| Actual Spam | 44 (FN)       | 106 (TP)       |

**Interpretation:**

* Very low false positives (only 4) → important emails rarely marked as spam
* Some false negatives (44) → some spam messages are missed
* Model is highly precise but slightly conservative

---

## 6. Limitations

1. TF-IDF does not capture word order or context
2. Model may not generalize well to new types of spam
3. Dataset imbalance affects recall performance
4. Some spam messages may still bypass detection (false negatives)

